# S03-T04: Graph System

## Objective
Port `Graph.vue` (153 lines, Canvas 2D) to React — thin-line tactical chart with gradient fill.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `src/features/hud/graph/Graph.tsx` accepts `series: RingBuffer<number>` and `label`, `unit`.
- Renders: 1px tactical line, low-opacity grid, subtle gradient fill under curve.
- Uses `RenderScheduler.NORMAL` priority.
- Auto-scaled Y-axis with min/max from current buffer window.

## Steps
1. Build `GraphEngine` (pure Canvas).
2. Wrap with `<Graph>` React component.
3. Add `GraphGrid` configuration (5×5 default, low-opacity cyan).
4. Implement gradient fill via `createLinearGradient`.

## Invariants
- No chart.js — strictly hand-rolled Canvas (per UI_REGULATION anti-patterns).
- No thick gradients, no pie charts, no business-analytics vibe.
- One graph instance = one Canvas; never share.
